## Frontend — React / JavaScript

### Component Rules
- Use functional components only — no class components
- All hooks must be called at the top level — never inside conditionals or loops
- One component per file
- Component files: PascalCase (`ReviewForm.jsx`, `ScoreGauge.jsx`)
- Service/util files: camelCase (`api.js`)

### State Management
- Use `useState` and `useEffect` from React — no external state library needed at this scale
- Lift state to the lowest common ancestor
- Keep components focused — pass data down via props, events up via callbacks

### API Calls
- All API calls live in `src/services/api.js`
- Use axios with a base instance configured from `REACT_APP_API_URL`
- Never call `fetch` or `axios` directly inside components
- Handle errors at the component level, not inside the service

### Styling
- All styles in `App.css` using CSS custom properties (variables)
- No inline styles except dynamic values (e.g. score color, bar width)
- No CSS-in-JS libraries
- Class names: kebab-case (`.issue-card`, `.bench-bar`)
- Dark theme by default — `--bg: #0b0e14`
- Design tokens defined in `:root` — never hardcode colors outside of variables

### Forms
- Never use HTML `<form>` tags — use `div` with `onClick` handlers
- Validate input client-side before sending to API
- Disable inputs and buttons during loading state
- Show inline error messages, not alerts

### Environment
- API base URL from `process.env.REACT_APP_API_URL`
- Never hardcode `localhost` URLs in component code

