## Git Conventions

- Never commit `.env` files
- Never commit `__pycache__/`, `.venv/`, `node_modules/`
- Branch naming: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`
- Commit messages: imperative present tense — "Add scorer service", "Fix datetime timezone bug"

---

## Security

- All secrets via environment variables — no exceptions
- GitHub token: minimum required scopes only (PR read + contents read)
- Groq API key: never exposed to frontend
- CORS: explicit allowed origins — never `allow_origins=["*"]` in production
- Never log raw diffs or API responses that may contain secrets

---

## Performance Notes

- Large diffs (500+ lines) may approach LLM context limits — keep this in mind when testing
- `selectinload()` is mandatory for relationship loading in async SQLAlchemy — lazy loading will raise `MissingGreenlet` errors
- `expire_on_commit=False` is set on the session factory — objects remain usable after commit without re-querying

